@*
    Help.cshtml - Help documentation view for PcApprovalDashboard component
    Displays help information about the Approval Dashboard component when viewed in WebVella page designer Help mode.
*@

<div class="pc-approval-dashboard-help">
    <h4>Approval Dashboard Component</h4>
    <p>
        The Approval Dashboard component displays real-time metrics and statistics for approval workflows in your WebVella ERP system.
        It provides managers and administrators with a quick overview of approval activity and performance.
    </p>

    <h5>Metrics Displayed</h5>
    <p>This dashboard displays the following 5 metric cards:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Pending Count</strong> - The total number of approval requests currently awaiting action.</li>
        <li><strong>Average Approval Time</strong> - The average time (in hours) taken to process approval requests.</li>
        <li><strong>Approval Rate</strong> - The percentage of requests that were approved versus rejected.</li>
        <li><strong>Overdue Count</strong> - The number of approval requests that have exceeded their SLA deadline.</li>
        <li><strong>Total Processed</strong> - The total number of approval requests that have been completed (approved, rejected, or cancelled).</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>Usage</h5>
    <p>
        Place this component on a manager or administrator dashboard page to provide visibility into approval workflow performance.
        The metrics update in real-time based on data from the approval_request and approval_history entities.
    </p>

    <h5>Configuration</h5>
    <p>
        Use the Options panel to configure the dashboard title and any filtering options for the metrics displayed.
    </p>
</div>

